  "texts": [
    "It is not enough to observe that a system has, with sufficient frequency, done the right thing so far.",
    "After all, it may be that a system has, in the past, done the right thing by mere luck, e.g.",
    "because its non-moral programming always happened to align with moral demands.",
    "In order to be reliably moral, it also needs to be the case that the system would do the right thing in a range of counterfactual situations we may put it in.",
    "But what criteria do we have to establish reliable performance in counterfactual or future situations?"
  ],
